    <section>
      <h2>1. What is Prime 2.0?</h2>
      <p>
        Prime is Hire Space's premium venue product. Historically, Prime campaign management (blog placements, Google Ads scheduling, search boosting) has been entirely manual, relying on spreadsheets and ad hoc coordination between the Growth team and venue partners.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Prime 2.0</strong> replaces that manual process with a self-service interface inside Venues HS, giving Prime venues direct control over how and where they appear across the platform. The result: less operational overhead for the team, faster turnaround for venues, and a more scalable product.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. The Three Modules</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Search Boost</h3>
      <p><strong>Status:</strong> âœ… Complete</p>
      <p>
        Each Prime venue can select up to <strong>3 keywords</strong> (e.g. "christmas party", "private dining", "conference") via a new section in Venues HS. Selecting a keyword boosts that venue's visibility across:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Platform search results</li>
        <li>Category pages (powered by search)</li>
        <li>Blog content matching those keywords</li>
        <li>Any search-driven surface on the site</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This gives venues meaningful control over their discoverability without requiring any manual intervention from the Hire Space team.
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Blog Campaigns</h3>
      <p><strong>Status:</strong> ðŸ”„ In code review</p>
      <p>
        Hire Space publishes a scheduled calendar of themed blog posts throughout the year (e.g. "Best Christmas Party Venues in London", "Top Summer Party Spaces"). Prime venues can sign up for up to <strong>3 blog placements per year</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>How it works:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Venue browses available blog slots in Venues HS, filtered by theme/event type</li>
        <li>Venue selects the blogs they want to appear in</li>
        <li>On execution, the backend calls the <code>blogCreation</code> endpoint, which generates the blog content via Ghost CMS, automatically including the venue's listing alongside other relevant venues</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Blogs are populated with a mix of Prime venue selections and algorithmically matched venues to fill remaining slots, ensuring quality and relevance.
      </p>

      <h3>2.3 Google Ads Campaigns</h3>
      <p><strong>Status:</strong> ðŸ”„ In code review</p>
      <p>
        Prime venues can schedule Google Display Ads campaigns directly from Venues HS. Each venue gets up to <strong>~2 campaigns per year</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>How it works:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Venue selects an event type and preferred week</li>
        <li>Campaigns run Monday to Friday (5 days)</li>
        <li>A weekly cron job (Saturday morning) locks campaigns and triggers the <code>scheduleGoogleAd</code> endpoint</li>
        <li>After the campaign completes, results (impressions, clicks) are fetched via the <code>fetchAdResults</code> endpoint and displayed to the venue</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Key constraints:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Maximum ~8 campaigns per week across all venues</li>
        <li>Start date must always be a Monday</li>
        <li>Campaigns cannot be scheduled too far in advance (Google Ads reliability issue)</li>
        <li>Campaign names must be unique, following the format: <code>Prime - [Venue Name] - [Month Year] - [Event Type] - [Unique ID]</code></li>
        <li>Campaigns are locked for editing at close of play Friday</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

